# Vercel CLI honors this file in preference to .gitignore. Without it
# the upload sweep picks up `desktop/release/` (the built DMG + Electron
# framework binary) and hits Vercel's 100 MB per-file upload limit.
#
# Keep this lean: only exclude things Vercel definitely doesn't need
# to build the web app. The desktop tree is a sibling artifact (built
# separately by .github/workflows/desktop-dmg.yml) and Vercel never
# needs any of it.

# Desktop Electron app + its build artifacts (DMG, Electron framework).
# Leading slash anchors to the ROOT desktop/ only — an unanchored `desktop/`
# ALSO matches src/components/desktop/, which silently dropped
# DesktopUninstallModal from CLI uploads and broke the production build.
/desktop/

# Local build output — Vercel runs its own build in the cloud
/dist/

# Deps + caches — Vercel installs cleanly
node_modules/
.cache/
.turbo/

# Secrets — should never leave the dev machine
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local

# OS / editor cruft
.DS_Store
*.log
.vscode/
.idea/

# Source maps (optional, keeps the upload lean — drop this line if you
# want the deploy to ship them)
*.map
